      "weather": "Fine",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DAME TRUCULENT (1) had a tough draw to overcome and was game in defeat when only 0.8 lengths from Pink Poppy Club in second (20.00) at this track. Has good early burn and is suited drawn on the inside. Sure to be about the mark. TIME OF DESIGN (4) is racing well without winning, recording three minors on end, the latest when checked in the run and finishing third in a TG1-4W at this track (20.24). Speedy runner who can find the front with a clear break off the middle. Key chance on best form. ONCE A DIVA (8) finds it hard to break through. Hit the board with a minor placing last time when third (20.06) at this track. Has performed well from this box with a win and five minor placings to her name from 12 starts. Must be included in calculations. EASY ACES (6) can return to form after missing the top-three at this circuit last time out.",
